					<b>
						Prevent muscle soreness
					</b>
					As well as unnecessary discomfort from juggling a desk phone
					handset a VoIP headset allows you keep your natural posture while making a call and
					avoiding any negative impacts from holding a traditional handset in an awkward pose
					for some time.
				</p>
				
				<br>
				
				<p>
					<b>
						Free up your hands
					</b>
					Continue to work on other tasks while you take calls. This can be a
					great benefit if taking queries or answering questions and also allows you to
					multitasks and improve productivity.
				</p>
				
				<br>
				<p>
					<b>
						Remain fully connected
					</b>
					Move freely around your office or other work environment
					without the hassle of wired connections. Like the point above, hands free headsets
					also allow you to continue to carry out tasks on the move.
				</p>
				
				<br>
